==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek '''plesio''', ''[[near]]'' + '''chronous''', [[time]]

===Adjective===
'''plesiochronous'''
#(communications) of or pertaining to the use of clocks derived from similar, but not the same reference clocks
#: ''The DS-3 standard uses bit stuffing to allow the clocks of its tributaries to be '''plesiochronous'''.'' 

